			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Limestone flour; Ground-up limestone; Dolomite</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Limestone flour; Ground-up limestone; Dolomite</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Organic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Limestone powder is made from ground-up rock, limestone, or dolomite, and is high in calcium. It is widely used in sewage treatment, waste incineration, building materials, desulfurization of power plants and ceramic plants, etc. It is also used in self-dense concrete. The main component of limestone is calcium carbonate (CaCO 3), usually in the form of calcite or aragonite. It may also contain magnesium carbonate (dolomite), clay, iron carbonate, feldspar, pyrite, and quartz.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">石灰石粉由磨碎的岩石、石灰石或白云石制成，含钙量高。它广泛用于污水处理、垃圾焚烧、建材、发电厂脱硫和陶瓷厂等。它还用于自密实混凝土。石灰石的主要成分是碳酸钙（CaCO 3），通常以方解石或文石的形式存在。它还可能含有碳酸镁（白云石）、粘土、碳酸铁、长石、黄铁矿和石英。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>CaCO3</sumFormula>
